  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0d86\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dba\u0db8\u0dca \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dba \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca QR \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0daf\u0dd2\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vehicle revenue license can be registered by QR method",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Electricity and Energy Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that for those who could not register for the fuel license based on the chassis number of the vehicle, they have now got the opportunity to register for the fuel license using the vehicle revenue license.",
        "He also says that 4.7 million vehicles have been registered for the fuel license so far. This number of vehicles had been registered by 8.30 last night.",
        "He said that 1060 petrol stations have tried this method and 746 petrol stations have distributed fuel through the fuel license yesterday. The number of transactions that have taken place through this is 1.1 million, the minister further said on his Twitter account."
      ],
